And the truth that we're looking at today will do that.

06:22.337 --> 06:23.699
No doubt about it.

06:24.099 --> 06:29.567
This story that we're looking at, you obviously just saw a clip of it, is the story of Jesus feeding the multitudes.

06:30.128 --> 06:32.071
And it shows up in all four of the gospels.

06:32.111 --> 06:34.034
We're gonna look at the Gospel of John,

06:34.306 --> 06:36.750
and look a little bit at how he addresses it.

06:36.770 --> 06:41.937
Because he has some unique details in his account that can really help us.

06:41.957 --> 06:47.505
So if you're here and you need some kind of miracle in your life, you got some kind of problem.

06:47.565 --> 06:52.292
It could be a financial problem, a relationship problem, a vocational problem, a school problem.

06:52.312 --> 06:57.079
I don't know what it is, but you have some kind of problem and there's not an obvious solution to it.

06:57.720 --> 06:59.122
You've tried some things.

06:59.554 --> 07:03.720
You've done everything you know how to do, and it's still not working out the way you want it to work out.

07:03.760 --> 07:06.163
If that's you, this message is just for you.

07:06.664 --> 07:07.905
And you're not here by accident.

07:07.945 --> 07:15.015
I believe that God has something that you need to hear and apply to your life if you find yourself in an impossible situation today.

07:15.516 --> 07:16.798
So let me kind of set this up for you.

07:16.818 --> 07:19.561
In the book of John, John's book is unique.

07:19.942 --> 07:21.063
John has an agenda.

07:21.344 --> 07:25.970
When John writes the Gospel of John, he clearly states that there's an agenda.

07:26.146 --> 07:31.173
And the agenda is he wants us to understand what it is that he saw and what it is that he heard.

07:31.634 --> 07:37.924
When John started to follow Jesus originally, he did not follow him because he thought he was the Messiah, right?

07:38.004 --> 07:46.036
When John begins to follow Jesus, he says, I started to follow Jesus because of what I saw him doing and when I heard him teaching.

07:46.656 --> 07:47.698
And eventually,

07:47.778 --> 07:55.550
As he saw the things that Jesus did and he heard the things that Jesus taught, John came to a place where he placed his faith in Jesus as his Messiah.

07:55.871 --> 07:58.595
He came to believe that Jesus was who he claimed to be.

07:59.116 --> 08:02.802
And his agenda in his gospel is that there's no confusion.

08:03.383 --> 08:10.674
He wants to lay out his account because he believes that if you could, with your mind's eyes, see what he saw.

08:11.170 --> 08:19.943
And with your mind's ears here, what he heard from Jesus, that you would come to the same conclusion that he did, that Jesus actually was who he claimed to be.

08:20.704 --> 08:31.561
So what you have to understand when John's all the way through the book of John, when he's describing these different signs, these different miracles, John doesn't want us just to see what Jesus did.

08:31.601 --> 08:35.026
He wants us to know who Jesus is.

08:35.746 --> 08:39.852
And what John is saying is he kind of organizes the gospel of John, the book of John.

08:40.133 --> 08:47.804
What he's trying to say is, hey, these random acts of kindness, these things that seem like random acts of kindness are actually not random at all.

08:48.365 --> 08:52.972
And there's more going on below the surface to the miracle that Jesus performed.

08:53.072 --> 08:56.517
It was this miracle feeding the multitude, that surface level.

08:56.898 --> 08:58.320
There's a lot more going on.

08:58.761 --> 09:02.226
And in every single miracle, what we're getting to see is another layer

09:02.338 --> 09:05.922
where Jesus is showing us more about the heart of God, about who He is.

09:06.342 --> 09:14.411
So I just wanna walk through this story, I know you just watched the video, but I wanna walk through this story so you can kinda hear John's perspective of how this event unfolded, all right?

09:14.852 --> 09:27.666
So John 6, first one, sometime after this, Jesus crossed to the far shore of the Sea of Galilee that is the Sea of Tiberius and a great crowd of people followed Him because they saw all the signs that He had performed by healing the sick.

09:27.874 --> 09:29.617
So again, John's laying it out there.

09:29.837 --> 09:32.582
You wanna know why there's a great crowd of people following Jesus?

09:32.962 --> 09:36.889
At this point, the reason they're following Him is they've seen the signs.

09:37.450 --> 09:38.572
They've seen the miracles.

09:38.852 --> 09:41.256
They've seen Him do things nobody else has ever done.

09:41.717 --> 09:48.007
And they don't know exactly who He is or what He's about at this point, but they know there's something different about this man.

09:48.047 --> 09:48.929
So they're following Him.

09:49.430 --> 09:52.395
Then Jesus went up on a mountain side and He sat down with His disciples.

09:52.435 --> 09:54.418
The Jewish Passover Festival was near.

09:54.498 --> 10:02.171
When Jesus looked up and he saw a great crowd coming towards him, he said to Philip, where shall we buy bread for these people to eat?

10:03.092 --> 10:06.839
He asked this only to test them, for he already had in mind what it is he was going to do.

10:07.219 --> 10:08.021
Philip answered him.

10:08.261 --> 10:14.231
It would take more than a half a year's wages to buy enough bread for each one to have just a bite.

10:15.073 --> 10:18.258
So Philip, he's kind of the number cruncher.

10:18.498 --> 10:23.204
He's gonna start crunching the numbers and he's like, okay, there's like 20,000 people here.

10:23.925 --> 10:25.867
This is how much it would cost.

10:25.887 --> 10:28.510
He eventually comes to the conclusion, right?

10:28.831 --> 10:29.632
This can't be done.

10:30.032 --> 10:34.898
We don't have enough money to even come close to feeding 20,000 people.

10:35.799 --> 10:47.794
Another one of his disciples, Andrew, Simon Peter's brother spoke up, here's a boy with five small barley loaves and two small fish, but how far will they go amongst so many?

10:48.386 --> 10:50.768
So you got Philip, he's the number cruncher, right?

10:51.029 --> 10:53.211
You've got Andrew, he's kind of the action guy.

10:54.112 --> 10:55.773
Philip's gonna try to solve this with math.

10:56.154 --> 11:00.318
It's like, I think in almost every family, there's like the number cruncher, right?

11:00.698 --> 11:04.462
They tend to be annoying, but they're needed, right?

11:04.922 --> 11:08.286
A family without a number cruncher is gonna go south pretty quick, right?

11:08.306 --> 11:10.468
So there's always one, and then there's the action person.

11:10.488 --> 11:16.914
This is Andrew, and he's just running around, he's costing a bunch of kids and stealing their lunch box, and he comes back,

11:16.994 --> 11:20.298
And he's like, all we have is two small fish and five loaves.

11:20.618 --> 11:26.986
So again, they both try to solve the problem in two different ways, but they come to the same solution, which is it can't be done.

11:27.006 --> 11:28.728
The problem is bigger than the solution.

11:29.309 --> 11:31.371
Jesus said, have the people sit down.

11:32.132 --> 11:33.454
There's plenty of grass in that place.

11:33.494 --> 11:35.636
They sat down about 5,000 men were there.

11:36.077 --> 11:39.661
So we're assuming the numbers probably around 20,000 total.

11:40.242 --> 11:43.666
Jesus then took the loaves, gave thanks and distributed those

11:43.746 --> 11:47.091
who were seated as much as they wanted, he did the same with the fish.

11:47.392 --> 11:53.662
When they had all enough to eat, he said to the disciples, gather the pieces that are left over, let nothing be wasted.

11:54.023 --> 12:00.233
So they gathered them and filled 12 baskets with the pieces of the five barley loaves left over by those who had eaten.

12:00.754 --> 12:06.784
So it's this cool story, but again, there's a lot more going on here than what you just see on the surface.

12:07.284 --> 12:08.306
You got Philip,

12:08.386 --> 12:12.890
and Andrew, kind of the two main characters that are in the midst of this drama.

12:12.910 --> 12:15.713
They're both trying to solve the problem, but they can't solve the problem.

12:15.733 --> 12:18.035
They don't think that there's a solution to this.

12:18.476 --> 12:19.717
They say it can't be done.

12:20.197 --> 12:23.981
It's impossible, but this is all kind of a test, right?

12:24.001 --> 12:24.942
That's what John says.

12:25.082 --> 12:30.047
It's all kind of a test because Jesus already knew what it was that he wanted to do.

12:30.647 --> 12:34.971
So when he asked the question, where should we buy bread for all these people to eat?

12:35.312 --> 12:37.874
The answer to the question is actually in

12:37.986 --> 12:40.610
the person who's asking the question.

12:41.431 --> 12:46.239
And yet somehow, in the midst of this scenario, even though they've already seen Jesus do miracles, right?

12:46.279 --> 12:47.381
John already pointed that out.

12:47.621 --> 12:52.329
In fact, the disciples in Jesus had just come from a location where he was doing many signs and wonders.

12:52.649 --> 13:03.987
It's why all these people are there, but when faced with a problem, an impossible situation, they failed to factor in that God in the flesh is standing right there in the middle of them, right?

13:04.007 --> 13:05.810
They just came from the experience.

13:06.306 --> 13:07.567
of watching him do miracles.

13:07.868 --> 13:11.111
But for some reason in this situation, it just feels impossible.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.613
And then interesting how we do the same thing.

13:14.815 --> 13:28.769
Like if I were to sit down with you and kind of like ask you to tell me the story of your life, I think for many of you, you could point to central spots throughout your story, throughout your life where God showed you up for you in a miraculous way.

13:29.790 --> 13:34.194
But whatever it is you're facing now feels new and it feels different.

13:34.658 --> 13:41.908
And trusting Him in this particular scenario that you find yourself in today feels heavier, feels weightier than the last time, right?

13:42.008 --> 13:44.472
And you're failing to factor God into the mix.

13:44.832 --> 13:52.543
I think the problem for the disciples on this day is that they're more focused on what they can't do than they are on what Jesus can do.

13:53.705 --> 13:57.090
Which is exactly what probably hundreds of you are doing right now.

13:57.731 --> 14:02.898
And whenever scenario you find yourself in, whatever situation it feels like it's impossible, whether it's a

14:03.170 --> 14:07.115
finance thing, a relationship thing, a vocational thing, right?

14:07.155 --> 14:17.628
Something to do with your, right now it feels impossible and you're so focused on what you can't do that you've forgotten about what Jesus can do, right?

14:17.648 --> 14:23.355
And I know there's a lot of you there because I've been there so many times throughout my life and I'll be there more times ahead.

14:24.056 --> 14:25.778
It is something inside of us, right?

14:26.118 --> 14:32.626
That often when faced with a difficult or impossible situation, we failed to factor in that got in the flesh.

14:33.474 --> 14:36.397
wants to help us, wants to partner with us, right?

14:36.818 --> 14:41.643
Doesn't expect for us in any way to do this on our own, right?

14:41.663 --> 14:46.668
So Philip and Andrew are trying to figure it all out in some ways they're failing to test, because it's not really a test, right?

14:46.968 --> 14:47.669
It's a setup.

14:48.030 --> 14:50.853
It's a setup to see if they'll look up, right?

14:51.073 --> 14:52.514
That's what's going on for you right now.

14:52.875 --> 14:56.198
I don't think it's so much of a test that God's given you as much as it's a setup.

14:56.619 --> 14:58.801
And the setup is, will you look up?

14:58.821 --> 15:03.346
When you find yourself in an impossible, difficult situation, will you look up?

15:04.802 --> 15:11.252
Now the good news for those of you who feel like your life is a mess right now, miracles always start with a mess.

15:12.193 --> 15:13.315
They always start with a mess.

15:13.936 --> 15:22.990
So if you're here today and there's some area of your life that feels like it's a mess, feels like it's impossible, feels like there's no solution to it, I would say to you, congratulations.

15:23.511 --> 15:27.357
Congratulations because you are in the first stage of a miracle.

15:28.279 --> 15:30.021
Because miracles always start with a mess.

15:31.363 --> 15:33.106
And some of you came in here today,

15:33.218 --> 15:57.381
or some of you watching online today, and maybe the situation is a health situation, and there's some pain, and nobody can figure it out, and you're just living with it day after day, but it feels impossible to you, maybe as to do with your finances, and you've crunched all the numbers, and you know what the bills are, and you know how much money you have, and you're like, this is not adding up, this is not good, right?

15:57.421 --> 16:02.546
And if I don't get that raise, if I don't get that promotion, if I don't get that new job, we're done.

16:02.690 --> 16:07.597
Maybe it's an addiction and it's something you fought on and off your entire life and you're tired of even fighting it.

16:07.798 --> 16:10.321
You're like, why would I keep trying to find freedom from this?

16:10.622 --> 16:13.887
Because every time it ends in the same way and I go right back to this.

16:14.247 --> 16:15.369
Maybe for you, it's a marriage.

16:15.830 --> 16:20.657
And you're like, there's not enough marriage therapists in all of Detroit to fix this marriage.

16:21.899 --> 16:32.114
For some of you, you wish it was a marriage issue because you're not married and you just really want to be married and you find yourself in a situation where you're ready just to give in and settle because it feels

16:32.290 --> 16:34.193
impossible, right?

16:34.253 --> 16:41.103
Maybe it has to do with your kids, and you've tried everything, but they're not going in the direction that you hope that they would go.

16:41.143 --> 16:46.131
Maybe it's a divorce that you've been through, and you just feel so beat down, you feel like you can't get back up.

16:46.651 --> 16:47.333
Here's what I know.

16:47.793 --> 16:51.078
Miracles always start with a mess.

16:52.580 --> 16:54.583
With some problems that I can't solve.

16:57.187 --> 17:01.714
So if you have a problem right now that you can't solve, you're in the first stage of a miracle.

17:02.306 --> 17:07.131
Now the temptation, right, when you find yourself in these situations is again, like Philip and Andrew.

17:07.752 --> 17:08.953
I'm gonna figure this out.

17:08.973 --> 17:10.555
I'm gonna run the numbers, right?

17:10.595 --> 17:13.137
I'm gonna develop a strategy here, right?

17:13.578 --> 17:20.485
But you're looking at the size of your problem and you're looking at the reality of what you have and you're like, this doesn't work.

17:21.886 --> 17:29.074
But the answer to the question that Jesus asked was actually in the question that he asked.

17:29.282 --> 17:34.708
I don't know if you saw this, it was verse five, we already read it, but he says, where shall we buy bread for these people to eat?

17:36.330 --> 17:37.111
You see the answer?

17:37.891 --> 17:38.292
It's we.

17:38.692 --> 17:42.136
Where shall we buy bread for these people to eat?

17:42.336 --> 17:46.000
Jesus never said to Philip, Philip, got a problem, you need to figure it out.

17:46.721 --> 17:48.063
Andrew, you need to figure it out.

17:48.103 --> 17:50.866
No, no, no, he says, what are we going to do?

17:50.886 --> 17:54.109
But they failed to factor that in, right?

17:54.710 --> 17:58.514
He's saying, listen, listen, right, if I remain in you,

17:59.042 --> 18:02.005
and you remain in me, you are very much true.

18:02.625 --> 18:05.148
But apart from me, you can do nothing.

18:05.688 --> 18:09.272
This is supposed to be a we thing, not a me thing.

18:09.312 --> 18:15.678
If you need a miracle in your life, you have to turn your me problem into a we problem.

18:16.659 --> 18:19.602
I turn my me problem into a we problem.

18:20.062 --> 18:28.210
The problem with turning your me problem into a we problem is that there's something inside of you as a human being that desires self-sufficiency.

18:29.378 --> 18:33.825
There's something inside of you right now that desperately wants to figure out your situation on your own.

18:34.406 --> 18:45.024
And you think that maybe you're smart enough or you're strong enough and your theme kind of in this situation or throughout most of your life has been, I got this, I got this, I can do this.

18:45.224 --> 18:48.931
There's something inside of all of us that wants it to be that way.

18:49.752 --> 18:53.458
I see this my youngest, I have four kids, my youngest is two and a half year old.

18:53.634 --> 19:00.046
Our name's Pepper, and I love telling stories about her, because she's not old enough to realize I'm telling stories about her yet, so I can get away with it.

19:00.086 --> 19:01.649
My others are old enough to realize.

19:01.729 --> 19:06.457
So I tell a lot of stories about Pepper, and this is the last week sometime.

19:06.958 --> 19:15.634
We have a little park in our neighborhood, and it's like most little parks for kids, got some swing sets, it's got a couple slides, a little tunnel you can crawl through.

19:15.714 --> 19:20.440
But in the backside of this little play area, it's got all this mulch and it's built into the side of the hill.

19:20.841 --> 19:25.748
So what they did is they brought in these big like boulders and kind of stacked them three or four high.

19:26.108 --> 19:32.457
So it's this wall that goes all the way around the playground that's holding that hill up.

19:32.477 --> 19:38.065
Well, you take your kids to this playground and none of the kids are actually playing on the playground equipment.

19:38.405 --> 19:40.748
They all want to play on those rocks, right?

19:40.808 --> 19:43.352
So all the kids are climbing the rocks and are walking along the rocks.

19:43.372 --> 19:44.914
So what's happened over the years

19:44.994 --> 19:53.102
is some of those big boulders have chipped away, and now there's some smaller rocks, but they're still big, like this big, that are on the ground, and the kids play on those too.

19:53.482 --> 19:57.226
As I'm describing this playground, I'm thinking, this is not a very safe playground to take your kids to.

19:57.286 --> 19:59.188
But she loves it.

19:59.208 --> 19:59.889
And so we go there.

19:59.909 --> 20:04.773
And the other day, she knew that the rock that was down in the playground wasn't supposed to be there, right?

20:04.833 --> 20:08.077
And so occasionally people pick them up and place them back up on the wall.

20:08.737 --> 20:12.021
And so I was like, do you think we should move the rock?

20:12.561 --> 20:13.522
And she was like, yes.

20:13.890 --> 20:16.313
And I was like, okay, we'll move the rock, right?

20:16.373 --> 20:23.642
And so I knew she couldn't move the rock as like three times what she weighs, but it was a fun few minutes as you're watching her struggle and trying to figure it out, right?

20:24.103 --> 20:32.053
And she's like, literally she's making these noise, like, I can do this, like I can pick up this rock, but she couldn't.

20:32.153 --> 20:36.078
And eventually I was like, Pepper, would you like dad to help you move that rock?

20:36.759 --> 20:39.122
And she was like, yes, that's a good idea.

20:39.330 --> 20:41.313
I'm like, yeah, it is a good idea, right?

20:41.373 --> 20:43.215
That's all you had to do is just ask, right?

20:43.295 --> 20:47.241
I never actually expected that you were going to move that on your own.

20:47.281 --> 20:51.306
There's something inside of us where we want to move it on our own.

20:51.607 --> 20:52.548
We want to figure it out.

20:52.728 --> 21:00.839
And all along, God just saying, hey, if you'll take your me problem and invite me into it, make it a we problem, you're going to get a lot more done.

21:00.880 --> 21:03.503
But there's something about this, that self-sufficiency.

21:03.743 --> 21:06.848
I even hear it in the language that sometimes we use as Christians.

21:06.868 --> 21:07.549
We make up things.

21:07.629 --> 21:08.530
I love Christians.

21:08.738 --> 21:09.959
